  "text": "This study was approved by the Institutional Review Board and the Animal Care and Use Committee at National Taiwan University. The survival rate of transfected MCF-7 cells was determined by counting cell numbers using trypan blue. Transfected MCF-7 cells (1 × 10 6 live cells in 100 μl Hank's balanced salt solution) were injected into the mammary fat pads of 5-week-old NOD SCID mice (supplied by the animal center at the College of Medicine, National Taiwan University). To determine whether miR-34b could reduce orthotopic tumor growth, the mice were randomized into two groups (n = 10 for each group): (1) miR-34b Tet-On overexpression stable clone without doxycycline (Sigma-Aldrich) or (2) miR-34b Tet-On overexpression clone with doxycycline. Mice were injected with doxycycline (2 mg/ml) in water [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] after tumor size reached 5 mm 3 . Tumor sizes were monitored every 7 days by using electronic vernier calipers, and the tumor volume (V) was calculated by using the formula V = 0.4 × ab 2 , where a and b are the longest and shortest diameters of each tumor, respectively.",
